Glucose lowering should be approached by managing overall cardiovascular risk. 
Glycemic goals should be individualized based on duration of diabetes, 
preexisting cardiovascular disease, age, and life expectancy. Intensive glycemic 
control has consistently been shown to produce a substantial benefit for 
preventing long-term microvascular complications in both type 1 and type 2 
